HEADWORD: Comment out
<hw>Com"ment` out"</hw> <pr>(k⟦ocr⟧m"m⟦ecr⟧nt out")</pr>, <pos>v.
t.</pos> <fld>(Computer science)</fld> <def>To add symbols in the code
of a computer program to convert (one or more lines of programming
statements) from executable instructions to comments; used to make
program statements inoperable without removing them permanently, such as
for temporary testing of alternative methods or to leave the original
lines in as explanatory comments.</def>⟦br⟧
